Text: I'm picking up on something strange.
Epsilon?
I can faintly sense it as well.

It feels as if...something is bending space. Epsilon,
can you pick up on anything more?
I'll give it a try.

It seems a powerful magic barrier is obstructing
our sense of direction.
You're saying someone is blocking us from advancing?!

...Guess that means we're getting closer to the
center of the Abyss Woods.

Zeta's right. We're on the right path, and someone or
something out there is trying to stop us.
I smell something strong over this way.
Doggo, quit breaking formation—
You really can't smell it, cat?!
Hmph!
She's right! There's something up ahead!
But what immense power... Alpha!

It must be something considerably dangerous if it's
enough to unsettle you.
Let's get closer and take it out! Whatever "it" is!
Dumb dog! Quit prancing ahead on your own!
Both of you! Come back—
No, let's have them go first.

We should trust their wild instincts rather than rely
on our distorted sense of direction.
But we don't know what awaits us ahead!

We seek the Garden's new home—turning back is not an
option. However...

Lambda, you take the other Garden members and head
back. If we don't return within three days, inform
Shadow.
Lady Alpha...

We face an opponent with unimaginable power. We can't
be certain the others will stand a chance.
...Very well. We'll withdraw immediately.

Travel safe, and give Eta my regards. We'll pursue
Delta and Zeta!
May you prevail!
That thing...is huge!
So...it is real!
Delta! Zeta!
Oh!
Who awakens me from my slumber...
Whoa!
Wh-What incredible magic force!

A surprising turn of events. They all look stunned,
not that I blame them.
The Mist Dragon!
There were those who once called me that...

But all have perished with the passing of time and
within the mist.
The ancient city of Alexandria as well?
Beta?!

You would rather seek the truth of a city lost to the
shadows of history than the fate that awaits you?

Even if you were to know, you would still die here
without ever having told a soul.
Still, I'm so curious!

I couldn't gather much intel, but I'd like to use
this opportunity to confirm if what I do have is
correct!

You would prefer that I corroborate your information?
Haha! Fascinating!

Very well... I suggest using the time I speak to
figure out a way to outsmart me!

What the heck? Turns out they both just like
chit-chatting.
Shh! Keep quiet, you dumb dog!

Some legends say the Mist Dragon ravaged the
prosperous city of Alexandria, laying waste to
it in a single night.

Others say it was the guardian of Alexandria who made
a pact with its king before betraying him and engulfing
the city in poison mist.

How's she conducting this mock interview under these
circumstances?

One of Beta's strengths is intellectual curiosity
that surpasses her own fears.

There's a degree of truth to that, but it hardly
represents all the facts.
Then what actually happened?!

In ancient times, I made a pact with the king of
Alexandria. It was a pact between two mighty
forces, promising prosperity for the city he
had established.

But the pact was eventually forgotten—its details,
its meaning, even my very existence.

Not only the people, no, but even the descendants of
the king whose kingdom I had continued to protect
beneath my fog had also all forgotten.

You were forgotten from their history? A considerable
amount of time must have passed then.

It was likely less than a millennium, which is a
fraction of time in terms of the existence of life
and the history of civilization.

Still, you could say that's a long, long time for a
human.

Indeed, it is the ephemeral nature of those whose
lives are mortal to be buried in the flow of time...

Did Alexandria's prosperity transform into corruption
over time?
Clever girl. You seem to have quite the imagination.

Yes, as the people of Alexandria grew jaded over
their prosperity, they lost the virtues of their
leaders who followed the ancient pact.
So...that's why you destroyed them?

With great power comes the need to prove one is
worthy of such power.

One such way is a ruler's virtue...along with dreams,
ambitions, determination, and a noble spirit.
A noble spirit...

So you sought a spirit worthy of power from the king
of Alexandria and its people?
I seek it not just from humans but from all life!

Those who lose their spirits and pursue only the
comforts of prosperity are not worthy of the
blessings such power bestows.

The lives and histories of other races pass in the
blink of an eye for dragons...

So because of how slowly time passes for dragons,
you place value in the spirit's relationship to
power?

I had hoped the wisdom brought to this new city by
the ancient king would transform the world and the
lives of those in it.

And I had hoped for the manifestation of spirit—the
power to stand up to the strong, to nurture one's
will, and to ascend higher as living beings!

You know what I mean, don't you, therianthrope? That
exhilarating moment you sense the presence of someone
powerful.

What're they talking about? Can't hear from this
distance...

Oh-woof, I do! Fighting against strong folk is super
exciting!

...So the city of Alexandria no longer sought
strength and fell into corruption—that's why
you destroyed it?!
Precisely!
Graarrr!!!
Eeeek?!

Their end was swift and unceremonious. That city,
once so prosperous, was destroyed by a simple
change in the direction of the billowing fog.

So you helped the city prosper and then destroyed it
with your own hands?

All that giving and taking just makes you one selfish
bastard...

Give and take... Exactly, therianthrope! Ultimately,
those are the only two things that move this world!

And you...who have ventured deep into this forest
will be given nothing...and have your lives taken
from you!
Yikes, looks like they've upset it.
Lady Alpha! What's our strategy—

It never let its guard down the whole time we were
talking. We'll have to work together to defeat the
dragon while avoiding its poison fog!
You mean fight it head-on?!

Tricks are not likely to work on it—this will be a
pure battle of strength!
A face-off and not a hunt... I'm getting excited!

Another passage soon to be added to the
legend of my existence!
Curiosity killed...the elves and therianthropes!
